# Universal Token Swap (Sprint 4)
#
# Circle App Kit's kit.swap()/kit.estimateSwap() require a "kit key" from
# the Circle Console to authenticate swap requests. Circle's own docs mark
# this as a credential ("do not log it, embed it in client-side source, or
# expose it in telemetry"). This project is a pure Vite/React frontend
# with no backend to proxy the call through, so this is a testnet-only
# tradeoff — the key still ends up in the client bundle. Rotate this key
# regularly and never use a mainnet/production kit key here. For a
# production deployment, proxy kit.swap()/kit.estimateSwap() through a
# backend so the key never ships to the browser.
VITE_SWAP_KIT_KEY=
